[1] Brazil (Rio de Janeiro)
Date: Thu 19 Feb 2009
Source: Abril [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.abril.com.br/noticias/brasil/dengue-pode-ter-matado-12-pessoas-rio-este-ano-273714.shtml>


Dengue may have caused the deaths of 12 people in Rio de Janeiro,
according to the figures the State Secretariat of Health released
today [19 Feb 2009]. These deaths, 3 in Rio de Janeiro, one case in
Queimados, Itaguai, Barra do Pirai, Sao Joao de Meriti, Mage,
Itaborai and Duque de Caxias and 2 cases in Sao Goncalo, are being
investigated, according to the Secretariat.

The registration of cases recorded up to yesterday [18 Jan 2009]
throughout the State of Rio recorded 2297 cases of dengue, 1918 in
January and 379 in February 2009. The 5 municipalities that
registered the greatest number of cases were Rio de Janeiro (783
[cases]), Itaborai (230), Niteroi (204) Angra dos Reis (142) and
Barra do Pirai (142).

[Byline: Solange Spigliatti]

--
