[6] Paraguay
Date: Thu 19 Feb 2009
Source: La Nacion [in Spanish, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.lanacion.com.py/noticias_um-231011.htm>


Dengue is slowly advancing in the national territory. Today [19 Feb
2009], the 1st confirmed cases of dengue were officially reported in
the city of Coronel Oviedo. According to the official report, 12
people have been infected by this virulent disease. In another
situation, Capiata has become the [dengue] focus in the Central
department, now that 5 more cases have been confirmed today [19 Feb
2009]. With these new cases, so far in the country, 173 cases have
been registered. Today [19 Feb 2009], 17 new cases were confirmed in
the departments of Caaguazu and Central. In Coronel Oviedo
(Caaguazu), a group of cases has been detected with a total of 34
reported [cases] during the risk period, of which 12 new cases were
confirmed, 4 by laboratory test results and 8 by epidemiological
connections. All the confirmed cases reside in Villa IPVU of Coronel
Oviedo city. With respect to the Central department, 5 confirmed
cases correspond to the Capiata district.

The total number of reported suspected cases during the latest 24
hour [period] were 39 from the following areas in the country: 7
[cases] in Asuncion, 5 in Amambay, 3 in Alto Parana, 7 in Caaguazu,
one de Pdte. Hayes, 2 in Concepcion and 22 reported from the Central
department.

--
Communicated by:
Health Map <promed@promedmail.org>

[The dengue cases appear to be dispersed across much of southern Paraguay.

